# Auction Context Engine Research

This project studies whether Low Volume Node (LVN) interactions are best used as a standalone trading strategy or as an auction-context layer that improves other models.

## Research result

The current 1H-structure / 15m-execution configuration produced 107 trades across the research sample with strong headline metrics, including a 71% win rate and profit factor above 4.

Despite these results, trade frequency remains relatively low for a primary standalone deployment engine. The more durable value of the research appears to be in the market-structure insights and reusable auction-context features.

## Main insight

The strongest signal quality comes from auction context:
- value acceptance before reversal
- LVN rejection/transition behaviour
- POC/HVN magnet logic
- context-aware filtering rather than candle cosmetics alone

## Best use cases

- BOS pre-trade filtering
- liquidity sweep quality scoring
- selective Telegram alerts
- discretionary dashboard features
- auction-context intelligence layer
